  "text": "We also denote by L n G (A) the set of word of length n in L G (A). We introduce the random variables S j i for j from 1 to n, i from 1 to n − j + 1 and S ∈ V taken from the filtering algorithm presented in [CITATION_1] . These binary variables follow a conditional distribution P M (V j i = 1 | X i , . . . , X i + j −1 ) which is equal to 1 if V → * X i . . . X i + j −1 and 0 otherwise. We therefore have:",
